<text>The H2O reaction: Measuring pressure increasing during explosion

&lt; Back &gt;

When an explosive reaction happens, a lot of the potential energy will be converted into the kinetic energy, thus we see a dramatical increasing of temperature and therefore pressure. This page presents you a setup to measure the increasing of pressure using the pressure gauge.

The X-Y graph only holds data for a certain length of the simulation. To increase the coverage, open the Task Manager (from the &quot;Option&gt;Task Manager&quot; menu of the Simulator&apos;s menu bar). In the row of &quot;Record the simulation&quot;, double-click the Interval cell and type in a new value (the default is 100). For example, putting 300 will triple the length of simulation the graph will cover.

  
&#12304;This is an embedded model container for chemical reactions.&#12305;

The pressure curve stablizes after the reaction completes. In reality, such a drastic increasing of pressure could blow up the container.

You can copy this page and use it as a starting point. Or learn how to use an X-Y graph from this section.

